Setting Up ESP32 in Arduino IDE
Before you start, you need to install the ESP32 board package in the Arduino IDE.

Step 1: Install ESP32 Board in Arduino IDE
Open Arduino IDE.
Go to File â†’ Preferences.
In the Additional Board Manager URLs, paste this: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
Click OK.
Now, go to Tools â†’ Board â†’ Boards Manager.
Search for ESP32 and install the latest ESP32 by Espressif Systems package.

Step 2: Select ESP32 Wrover Module

Step 3: Install ESP32 Drivers (Fix Missing COM Port)
ðŸ”¹ If the port is not showing in Device Manager, reinstall the USB driver.

  For CP2102-based ESP32 Boards (Most Common)
Download the latest CP210x USB to UART Bridge VCP Driver from:
https://www.silabs.com/developers/usb-to-uart-bridge-vcp-drivers
Go to Download section and Install it and restart your PC.

If your port is not being detected,
Go to your Device Manager -> Ports -> Silicon Labs CP210X USB to UART Bridge(COM Number)
